{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Emerald Hill Cricket Ground | nickname = | country = Australia | image = | location = [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]] | establishment = 1852 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | club1 = [[Victoria cricket team|Victoria]] | year1 = 1852 | date = 21 October | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/115.html Ground profile }}
'''Emerald Hill Cricket Ground''' (also known as the '''Melbourne Cricket Club Ground''' and '''South Yarra Ground''') was a [[cricket ground]] in [[Melbourne]], Victoria, Australia. The ground held the second ever [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match to be played in Australia when [[Victoria cricket team|Victoria]] played [[Tasmania cricket team|Tasmania]] in March 1852.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/115_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Emerald Hill, Melbourne|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref> The match was won by Victoria by 61 runs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/0/933.html|title=Victoria v Tasmania, 1851/52|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref> The last recorded match came on 5 January 1888 when Yarra Bend played GF Vernon's XI.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/2/115_misc.html|title=Yarra Bend v GF Vernon's XI, 1887/88|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref>
