The '''National Competition of Horsemen''' ({{lang-is|Landsmót hestamanna}}) is a [[sport|sporting event]] for [[horse racing]] and [[Animal husbandry|breeding]] [[exhibition]] of [[Icelandic horse]]s in [[Iceland]].  The event was first held 6 June 1950 at [[Þingvellir]] by the [[Icelandic Equestrian Association]] which was founded in December the year before for the purpose of running the event.  In the beginning the event was held every 4 years but since 1995 it was held every 2 years. In 2001 operational changes took place and the event is now annual and run by Landsmót hestamanna ehf, a company owned by the Icelandic Equestrian Association and the [[Farmers' Association of Iceland]].

