{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox stadium | name = South Eastern Railway Stadium | nickname = SER Stadium | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = South Eastern Railway Stadium | former names = SERA Stadiun | location = [[Visakhapatnam]], [[Andhra Pradesh]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1964 | built = | opened = 1964 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[South Eastern Railway zone|South Eastern Railway]] | operator = [[South Eastern Railway zone|South Eastern Railway]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = n/a | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/58544.html Cricinfo] | publictransit = }} '''South Eastern Railway Stadium''' is a multi purpose stadium in [[Visakhapatnam]], [[Andhra Pradesh]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket and other sports. The stadium has hosted a [[First-class cricket|first-class]] matches<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1278_f.html First-class matches]</ref> in 1964 when [[Andhra cricket team]] played against [[Hyderabad cricket team]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/27/27209.html Scorecard]</ref> The ground has held 7 further first-class matches, the last of which came in the 1997/98 [[Ranji Trophy]] when [[Andhra cricket team]] and the [[Goa cricket team]].
