{{infobox country at games | NPC = SUD | NPCname = Sudan National Paralympic Committee | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1980 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Arnhem]] | competitors = 11 | sports = 3 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 1 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} The '''[[Sudan]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games|Paralympic]] début at the '''[[1980 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Arnhem]]. The country was represented by eleven athletes competing in track and field, swimming and table tennis.<ref>{{IPC medals | npc = SUD }}</ref>
The Sudan won a single medal, when [[Mohamad Ahmed Isam]] took gold in the men's [[shot put]], 1B category.<ref>{{IPC medals | npc = SUD }}</ref>
This was to be the Sudan's last participation in the Paralympic Games before [[Sudan at the 2004 Summer Paralympics|2004]].<ref>{{IPC medals | npc = SUD }}</ref>
