{{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= Triathlon Association of the Philippines |logo= Triathlon Association of the Philippines.png |size= |sport= [[Triathlon]] |abbrev= TRAP |founded= |recognized= |association= [[Asian Triathlon Confederation|ASTC]] |headquarters= |president = Ramon Marchan<ref name="psa award">{{cite news|url=https://sports.abs-cbn.com/generalsports/news/2018/02/22/triathlon-association-honored-nsa-year-38012|title=Triathlon association to be honored as NSA of the Year|publisher=[[ABS-CBN Sports]]|date=February 22, 2018|accessdate=February 22, 2018}}</ref> |vicepresident = |secretary= Tom Carrasco<ref name="psa award"/> |url= triathlon.org.ph |countryflag= Philippines |code= PHI }}
The '''Triathlon Association of the Philippines''' is the national [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for [[Triathlon]] in the [[Philippines]]. It is accredited by the [[International Triathlon Union]] which is the governing body for the sport of Triathlon in the world. The association is also a member of the Asian Triathlon Confederation. The Asian Triathlon Confederation gave the Triathlon Association of the Philippines "developed status" in its 2014 and 2015 evaluation of its members in the areas of technical officials, coaches development and athletes development.<ref>{{cite news|title=Triathlon gets Asian citation|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/triathlon-gets-asian-citation/|accessdate=3 January 2015|publisher=Manila Bulletin|date=1 January 2015}}</ref</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://malaya.com.ph/business-news/sports/2-one-triathlon-event-set-subic|title=2-IN-ONE TRIATHLON EVENT SET IN SUBIC|publisher=Malaya|date=4 January 2016|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>
On February 27, 2018, TRAP was awarded as the National Sports Association of the Year in the [[2018 PSA Annual Awards|Philippine Sportswriters Association Annual Awards]], citing their gold medal finishes in Men's and Women's Triathlon events in the [[2017 Southeast Asian Games]] in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]].<ref name="psa award"/>
